description: Let’s talk about the REAL price of a car. Let me preface this by saying I absolutely love my van. It’s literally my dream mom-mobile. I really be running through the 6 with my woes in this bad boy 😂😂😂 but DAMN if I don’t cringe every time I have to buy something for it😩😩 On top of the cost of the car (and if you’re financing the interest you’ll be paying until it’s paid off), there’s preventative maintenance, emergency maintenance, car insurance, GAS IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA(🤬), car washes because my baby is a dirt magnet, details cause gang and them in the back are gross, like the list goes on and on. Now I’m lucky, this wasn’t my first rodeo with a new car. So as we shopped around I took into account all the costs associated with purchasing + maintaining my car. But a lot of people don’t. How much are oil changes? How often will you drive it? Will you need to change it often? What’s the going rate for tires? Do these things hold value? There’s so much that goes into being a car owner 😩😩 What are some things people should consider when car shopping?
